    {
      "type": "header",
      "content":"Template Assignment Rules"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content":"Template assignments will include the content type (page, blog, product, etc) and, if there is one, the name of the template (about, refer-a-friend,etc). Example below are using commas to show separation, but use newline inside inputs"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content":"TEMPLATE EXAMPLES: page, page.about, collection, collection.alternate."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content":"Url Assignment Rules"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content":"Url assignments should only use the part of the url after the '.com'. Example below are using commas to show separation, but use newline inside inputs"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content":"URL EXAMPLES: /pages/about, /pages/trade, /collections/all, /products/adrian-classic-tote"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content":"Overlay Header"
    },
    {
      "type": "liquid",
      "id": "overlay_header_template",
      "label": "Overlay header on Desktop."
    },

    {
      "type": "header",
      "content":"Desktop Display Settings"
